cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper proposes an unsupervised online learning approach based on a convolutional neural network (CNN) for optical flow estimation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of spatially variant motion models, which involves learning motion models for each frame individually, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of motion models to improve performance at occlusions, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, suggesting that it could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
